@NODE "Vorworteng" "Vorwort"
@TOC "MAIN"


                       Why do you need »GfxClip«?

   Do you looking for the possibility to create a graphic for different
   pages in your document?

   You working on a document with different sections. And now you need
   the same graphics at the background.
   You will create the graphics at the master pages and copy these graphics.
   Then you will paste they into the next master pages at an other section.
   But whats that? They will not be pasted at the correctly position...

   This script solves this problem.


   It's F R E E W A R E.

                                 Heiko Schröder    Leipzig, 06/14/98

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Braucheng" "What you need..."
@TOC "MAIN"

   - FinalWriter ;-)

   - RexxMast             - at your system

   - RexxReqTools.library (© Rafael D`Halleweyn - latest version: 37.95)
                          - available with this script

   - ReqTools.library     (© Nico François      - latest version: 38.1443)
        available at:
            Aminet - util/libs/ReqToolUsr.lha

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installeng" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

SYSTEM:

   Copy the "rexxreqtools.library.library" to your LIBS: directory.


FINALWRITER:

1. Copy »GfxClip.fwrexx« to your FWMacros-Drawer.

2. Start program »RexxMast«.

3. Start »Finalwriter« or »FinalCopyII«.

4. Open menu "User - Other - Preferences...". 

         * "Action" - New
         * "Name of menu" - GfxClip
         * "Command" - "Type" - ARexx-Script
         * "Command" - "Select" (GfxClip.fwrexx)
         * "HotKey" - (e.g. F10)
         * "Accept"
         * "Save"

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Benutzeng" "Usage"
@TOC "MAIN"

         Select the object(s) do you want to copy.
         Start this macro with the shortcut (e.g. F10).

         A requester will be opened, where you have to declare the
         name of the macro which will be created.
         The script saves the object(s) as a ARexx macro.

                                 That's all.

         Now your are able to join the object(s) to a new master page
         or a new document
         Start it with menu: User | Other | Arexx Script...

         @{fg shine}ATTENTION@{fg text}: The functions "Text Frames" and "Tables" will
                  be @{u}not@{uu} supported yet.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Tempseng" "The templates"
@TOC "MAIN"

   In Aminet you will find a file called »FW_GfxClipTemp.lha«.
   This file includes ready-to-use templates for Final Writer. 

   At the time you will find the following templates:

     * Arrow - Pfeil -> a line with two arrows


   If you also have created some templates with "GfcClip" and you mean
   that the other users would also need these please send they to me.
   I will upload this in »FW_GfxClipTemp.lha« to Aminet.

   My EMail-Adress: age@thepentagon.com
   Please write some words about you.

@ENDNODE

